# Introduction

This is a primitive version of reserbot. This bot tries to learn natural languages learning from imitation. 
Now, it is possible to try to teach knowledge using an artificial language called tokipona:

"Toki Pona is a simple language designed to express the most, using the least. The entire language has only 123 words 
and 14 sounds. The grammar, although different from English, is very regular and easy to learn." 
(from http://en.tokipona.org/wiki/What_is_Toki_Pona%3F)

# Requirements (so far):
 * Python 2.7 (I'm not sure about other versions)
 * Oger (http://reservoir-computing.org/organic/engine)

# How to use it:
 python src/main.py tokipona

# Example session
In this example session reserbot is taught to:
* say pona if you say toki (at first of the conversation)
* say nasa if you say telo (at first of the conversation)

--> load
Loading bootstrapped neurosequencers.
Loading seqLetterSyllable
Loading seqSyllableWord
Loading seqWordPhrase
Loading seqWordSyllables
Loading seqSyllableLetters
Loading seqPhraseWords
--> start
Conversation started.
--> say toki .
Processing "toki ."
<== s-s-s- k-t-t- k-te-t- 
--> say pona .
Processing "pona ."
<== k-te-tei- k-wei-t- k-te-t- 
--> end
Conversation ended.
--> start
Conversation started.
--> say telo .
Processing "telo ."
<== s-se-s- k-se-t- k-tep-p- 
--> say nasa .
Processing "nasa ."
<== m-tei-tei- k-tei-t- k-te-t- 
--> end
Conversation ended.
--> rest
Resting ...
na-ua-ua- .- .- 
ko-na-ua- k-ua-ua- k-ua-ua- 
---
